title: Filter Demo
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Filter-Based Outline Demo

This demo uses `++` filter lines to populate outline sections from the live tiddler store.  The first section is fully dynamic — every tiddler tagged `HistoryOfComputing` appears automatically.  The second mixes a filter with hand-picked static items.

<$simple-outline text="""
!! All History Notes (filter-generated)
  ++ [tag[HistoryOfComputing]sort[title]]

!! Hand-Picked Highlights (static)
  + note-turing-machines
  + note-von-neumann-architecture
  + note-unix-origins
""" class="outline" open-depth="1" label-fields="summary caption"/>

---

Try it: create a new tiddler, add `tags: HistoryOfComputing` to it, and watch it appear in the first section automatically.
